'''Thalente Wandile Mbatha''' (born 6 March 2000) is a South African [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a defensive midfielder for [[Premier Soccer League]] side [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

Mbatha scored on his international debut in 2024 against Uganda.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mark |first=Jonty |date=2024-09-06 |title=Mbatha strikes late to earn Bafana AFCON draw with Uganda |url=https://www.citizen.co.za/sport/soccer/local-soccer/uganda-stun-bafana-mothwa-blunder/ |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=The Citizen |language=en}}</ref>

== Club career ==
At the age of 10, Thalente Mbatha began his football journey with local amateur club Real Rabbits, where he played for the Under-11, Under-13, and Under-15 teams. By the time he was 13, his talent saw him competing across multiple age groups, featuring for the Under-13, Under-15, and Under-17 squads.

As he progressed through his teenage years, he joined Durban FC, further developing his skills and gaining recognition. His performances earned him a move to professional football, where he signed with Highlands Park FC in the South African Premier League.

=== SuperSport United ===
He played for Tshwane based side [[SuperSport United F.C.|SuperSport United]].<ref>{{Soccerway|thalente-mbatha/647929}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Qoshe |first=Yolulwe |date=2024-03-08 |title=SuperSport United clarify conditions of Talent Mbatha's Orlando Pirates move |url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/sport/soccer/psl-south-africa/supersport-united-clarify-conditions-of-talent-mbathas-orlando-pirates-move/ |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=The South African |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

=== Orlando Pirates ===
In January 2024, he joined Soweto based club [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] on a 6-month contract with the option for a permanent move.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-05 |title=Mbatha pressing to make Orlando Pirates loan transfer from SuperSport United a permanent move {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/mbatha-pressing-to-make-orlando-pirates-loan-transfer-from-supersport-united-a-permanent-move/blt1f957c3813ecca48#cs2f1331349e9b54fe |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He played his first final in the [[2023–24 Nedbank Cup|2023-24 Nedbank Cup]] final against [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]]. Mbatha was voted man of the match in the 2-1 win for Pirates.<ref>{{cite web | title=Nedbank Cup: Orlando Pirates' Thalente Mbatha Gets SA's Praise After Win over Mamelodi Sundowns - Briefly.co.za | date=2 June 2024 | url=https://briefly.co.za/sports/football/188441-nedbank-cup-orlando-pirates-thalente-mbatha-sas-praises-win-mamelodi-sundowns/ }}</ref> His deal was extended for the [[2024–25 South African Premiership|2024-25 PSL season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Agent confirms Mbatha stay at Pirates |url=https://supersport.com/football/general/news/7e69f39e-4297-44f7-9490-286c89dc8653/agent-confirms-mbatha-stay-at-pirates |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=SuperSport |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
Mbatha debuted for the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa men's national team]] in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|2025 Afcon qualifiers]] on 6 September 2024 against [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] and scored on debut to help the side salvage a draw.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ngidi |first=Njabulo |title=The rise and rise of Thalente Mbatha: 'He is going to be one of the biggest talents in SA' |url=https://www.news24.com/sport/soccer/bafanabafana/the-rise-and-rise-of-thalente-mbatha-he-is-going-to-be-to-be-one-of-the-biggest-talents-in-sa-20240904 |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=Sport |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ntshangase |first=Otis |date=2024-09-07 |title=Thalente Mbatha opens up on his Bafana Bafana heroics |url=https://farpost.co.za/2024/09/07/thalente-mbatha-opens-up-on-his-bafana-bafana-heroics/ |access-date=2024-09-07 |website=FARPost |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

On 1 December 2025, Mbatha was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

